The paper focuses on developing a formulation of graph-based SLAM, which is a common topic in robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses incorporating information from maps, which involves computer vision techniques (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The optimization of the graph involves using robust kernels, which is a machine learning technique (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses navigation and exploration, which falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY).
